Cherenkov radiation is valuable for Pantheon not because of nuclear physics itself, but because it embodies several transferable computational and informational invariants.

Physical invariant

A charged particle moves through a medium faster than light can travel through that medium (not faster than light in a vacuum).

Instead of the medium responding quietly, it cannot “get out of the way” fast enough.

The result is:

Stored polarization → coherent release → visible blue shockwave.

The glow is the medium revealing that something exceptional just passed through.

