Research Applications

Cherenkov-inspired operators could help Pantheon:

* Detect emerging scientific paradigms before they become mainstream.
* Identify influential ideas whose originators receive little recognition.
* Infer hidden coordination or common upstream influences from distributed downstream behavior.
* Estimate the “refractive index” of different communities—that is, how readily they absorb versus resist new ideas.
* Measure innovation efficiency by comparing original work with the scale of its downstream wake.

