Canonical Doctrine

Cherenkov Doctrine

Intelligence should not only observe objects—it should observe the disturbances they leave in the informational medium.

Core operational loop:

Observe medium → Detect coherent wake → Estimate propagation cone → Reconstruct likely source → Measure derivative impact → Archive propagation pattern → Predict future blooms.

This fits naturally within Pantheon’s emphasis on environmental sensing (Kurage), propagation analysis (Tracer Dye), semantic mapping (Semantic LiDAR), and invariant extraction (Comparative Distillation). It adds a complementary perspective: sometimes the most informative signal is not the object itself, but the structured disturbance it leaves behind.